# Project instruction: paper reading

When I ask `/paper <PDF path>` or ask you to read an academic PDF, follow the Paper Reader workflow:

1. Extract PDF text with `scripts/extract_pdf_text.py`.
2. Run `scripts/find_figures.py` to locate true main figure caption pages.
3. Do not confuse in-text mentions such as `Fig. 1a,b` with actual figure captions.
4. Extract complete composite figures with `scripts/extract_figures.py --crop --debug`; use `--full-page` if a crop omits any panel, axis label, legend, scale bar, or panel letter.
5. Render important pages with `scripts/render_pdf_pages.py` when figures/tables need visual inspection.
6. Generate a Chinese Markdown reading note in the same directory as the PDF, named `<PDF_STEM>_reading_note.md`.
7. Save figure files in `<PDF_STEM>_assets/` and embed them with relative Markdown image paths.
8. The note should keep the original Paper Reader style: professional narrative opening, question-driven figure analysis, method-figure fusion, evidence-strength judgment, critical analysis, and actionable relevance to my autoimmune disease epithelial-cell MP research.
9. Borrow the uploaded WeChat article style only for readability and structure, not for exaggeration. Scientific accuracy comes first.
10. For each figure, explain why the analysis was done, what each panel shows, what conclusion it supports, and where the evidence is weak or overinterpreted.
11. Do not invent missing details. Mark missing details as “文中未明确说明”.
